\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural
\cf0 Notice how I've replaced "damage" with "playerhit" and "enemyhit"? This is so that you can reference the strength of the player's attack and the enemy's attack separately if you ever need to. (although it's unlikely that you ever will) You can change these variables to whatever you like. You might prefer "playerdamage" or "playerD". I personally always use "playerhit" though. Finally, notice how Card 4 is loaded when the player is defeated? That's because Card 4 will serve as our Game Over Card. You don't need much code on that Card, just draw a game over picture and make a button that goes back to Card 1 or quits the game.\
